# AI Job Agent Platform

AI-first job search platform: ingest jobs, embed in pgvector, semantically match CVs, score with LLM, generate documents, surface apply links, track applications.

## Source of truth

Before implementing features, read:

- `docs/system-requirements.md` — MVP checklist
- `docs/tech-stack.md` — approved technologies only
- `docs/adr/` — binding architectural decisions
- `README.md` — project entry point and structure

Do not introduce technologies rejected in ADRs (e.g. Playwright for apply automation or DIY scraping as primary).

## Monorepo layout

```
backend/app/{api,core,db,models,schemas,services}/  — FastAPI
backend/{alembic,tests}/                              — migrations, tests
frontend/{app,components,lib,styles}/                 — Next.js (scaffold)
infra/{docker,deployment}/                            — containers, deploy
docs/{adr,system-requirements.md,tech-stack.md}       — requirements & ADRs
```

## Code principles

- Minimize scope; match existing conventions
- Business logic in `services/`, not route handlers
- Long-running work via ARQ workers, not request handlers
- Schema changes require Alembic migrations
- Significant architecture changes → new ADR in `docs/adr/`
